(1, 'What is 51st in word form?', 'Fifty third', 'Fifty-first', 'Fifty-one', 'Fifty second', 'Fifty-first', 'We write 51st as fifty-first. The number 51 is fifty-one, and when we talk about position or order, we add ''first'' instead of ''one''.', 'Medium'),
(1, 'What is 39th in word form?', 'Thirty eighth', 'Thirty-nine', 'Thirty-ninth', 'Thirty first', 'Thirty-ninth', 'The number 39 becomes thirty-ninth when we write it in order form. We change ''nine'' to ''ninth''.', 'Medium'),
(1, 'What is 20th in word form?', 'Twenty one', 'Twentieth', 'Twenty', 'Twentiethy', 'Twentieth', 'The word form of 20th is twentieth. We remove the ''y'' in twenty and add ''ieth''.', 'Medium'),
(1, 'What is fifteenth in number form?', '50th', '15', '5th', '15th', '15th', 'Fifteenth means the number 15 in order form, so it is written as 15th.', 'Medium'),
(1, 'What is twenty-third in number form?', '20th', '33rd', '23rd', '32nd', '23rd', 'Twenty-third means 23 in order form, so we write it as 23rd.', 'Medium'),
(1, 'What is twelfth in number form?', '21st', '12th', '2nd', '20th', '12th', 'Twelfth means the number 12 in order form, written as 12th.', 'Medium'),
(1, 'What is XI in number form?', '12', '10', '11', '9', '11', 'In Roman numerals, X means 10 and I means 1. When we add them, XI equals 11.', 'Medium'),
