(1, 'What is XLIV in number form?', '54', '46', '40', '44', '44', 'XL means 40 and IV means 4. Adding them gives 44.', 'Medium'),
(1, 'VI _ VI', 'â‰ ', '=', '<', '>', '=', 'Both sides show the same Roman numeral, VI, which means 6. Since they are equal, the correct symbol is =.', 'Medium'),
