(2, 'What is the masculine noun for a chicken?', 'hen', 'rooster', 'chick', 'duck', 'rooster', 'Rooster is the male chicken.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'What is the feminine noun for a parent?', 'father', 'mother', 'son', 'brother', 'mother', 'Mother is feminine.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'What is the feminine noun for sibling?', 'brother', 'sister', 'father', 'uncle', 'sister', 'Sister is feminine.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'What is the feminine noun for a chicken?', 'Rooster', 'Hen', 'Ram', 'Doe', 'Hen', 'Hen is the feminine noun for a chicken.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'What is the feminine noun for deer?', 'Doe', 'Hen', 'Cow', 'Ewe', 'Doe', 'Doe is the feminine noun for deer.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'Which ''c'' word has the same ''s'' sound as cell?', 'Citrus', 'Cat', 'Cup', 'Corn', 'Citrus', 'C has an ''s'' sound before i.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'Which ''c'' word has the same ''s'' sound as center?', 'Card', 'Cold', 'Cement', 'Circle', 'Cement', 'C has an ''s'' sound before e.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'Which ''c'' word has the same ''k'' sound as corner?', 'Cell', 'Card', 'City', 'Cement', 'Card', 'C has a ''k'' sound before a.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'Which ''c'' word has the same ''k'' sound as cut?', 'City', 'Cement', 'Come', 'Circle', 'Come', 'C has a ''k'' sound before o.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'Which word makes a compound word with rain?', 'Drop', 'Fall', 'Bow', 'Coat', 'Coat', 'Raincoat is a compound word.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'Which word makes a compound word with basket?', 'Cover', 'Case', 'Ball', 'Net', 'Ball', 'Basketball is a compound word.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'Which word makes a compound word with match?', 'Box', 'Stick', 'Fire', 'Light', 'Box', 'Matchbox is a compound word.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'Which word makes a compound word with birth?', 'Time', 'Place', 'Date', 'Day', 'Day', 'Birthday is a compound word.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'Which word makes a compound word with sun?', 'Ray', 'Heat', 'Shine', 'Light', 'Shine', 'Sunshine is a compound word.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''The house is big and beautiful'' What pronoun does ''house'' use?', 'They', 'It', 'He', 'She', 'It', 'House is a thing.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''Sera is my eldest sister'' What pronoun does ''Sera'' use?', 'They', 'He', 'She', 'It', 'She', 'Sera is a girl.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''My father and I clean our house every weekend'' What pronoun is used?', 'They', 'Us', 'He', 'We', 'We', 'Father and I means we.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''My brother lends me his books'' What pronoun does ''brother'' use?', 'He', 'They', 'She', 'It', 'He', 'Brother is male.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''The children in our neighborhood are my friends'' What pronoun is used?', 'We', 'They', 'Them', 'It', 'They', 'Children is plural.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''The school is near my house'' What pronoun does ''school'' use?', 'He', 'They', 'She', 'It', 'It', 'School is a thing.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''Mrs. Cruz is my class adviser'' What pronoun does ''Mrs. Cruz'' use?', 'He', 'They', 'It', 'She', 'She', 'Mrs. Cruz is female.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''English is my favorite subject'' What pronoun does ''English'' use?', 'They', 'It', 'He', 'She', 'It', 'English is a thing.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''My name is Samantha. ___ am in Grade 2''', 'She', 'We', 'I', 'They', 'I', 'I is used when talking about yourself.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''Mikasa and Armin are my friends. ___ are also my classmates''', 'We', 'Them', 'He', 'They', 'They', 'Two people use they.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''Riza is good in reading and writing. ___ has a collection of books''', 'He', 'She', 'They', 'It', 'She', 'Riza is female.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''Roy and I went to the library. ___ found many books to read''', 'They', 'Us', 'We', 'I', 'We', 'Roy and I means we.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''Books are very important. ___ gives us plenty of information''', 'It', 'They', 'He', 'She', 'It', 'The sentence refers to books as a thing.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''Edwards loves to play, ___ always plays in the park''', 'They', 'She', 'It', 'He', 'He', 'Edwards is male.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'Which word has the same ''g'' sound as game?', 'Giraffe', 'Glow', 'Giant', 'Gentle', 'Glow', 'Hard g sound.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'Which word has the same ''g'' sound as gender?', 'Ground', 'Game', 'Glow', 'Giraffe', 'Giraffe', 'Soft g sound.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'Which word has the same ''g'' sound as energy?', 'Glow', 'Ginger', 'Game', 'Ground', 'Ginger', 'Soft g sound.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'Which word has the same ''g'' sound as huge?', 'Genie', 'Ground', 'Game', 'Glow', 'Genie', 'Soft g sound.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'Which word has the same ''g'' sound as give?', 'Giraffe', 'Genie', 'Ground', 'Gentle', 'Ground', 'Hard g sound.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''Clarissa went home early'' What pronoun can replace ''Clarissa''?', 'He', 'They', 'She', 'It', 'She', 'Clarissa is female.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''Tommy kept the toys inside the cabinet'' What pronoun replaces ''the toys''?', 'They', 'It', 'Them', 'Us', 'Them', 'Toys is plural.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''Mr. and Mrs. Santos attended the program'' What pronoun replaces them?', 'We', 'They', 'Them', 'He', 'They', 'Two people use they.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''Mrs. Cruz watched her son sing a song'' What pronoun replaces ''her son''?', 'He', 'Him', 'Them', 'It', 'Him', 'Son is male.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''Daniel hugged his mother after his game'' What pronoun replaces ''his mother''?', 'She', 'Them', 'It', 'Her', 'Her', 'Mother is female.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''The program was a success'' What pronoun replaces ''the program''?', 'They', 'He', 'It', 'She', 'It', 'Program is a thing.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''My classmates and I went home after class'' What pronoun replaces it?', 'They', 'Us', 'Them', 'We', 'We', 'Classmates and I means we.', 'Medium'),
(2, '''The teacher thanked my parents and I for coming'' What pronoun replaces it?', 'Us', 'We', 'They', 'Them', 'Us', 'Object pronoun is used.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'Which word has the same ''th'' sound as thank?', 'This', 'Then', 'That', 'Thin', 'Thin', 'Voiceless th sound.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'Which word has the same ''th'' sound as third?', 'That', 'Math', 'These', 'They', 'Math', 'Voiceless th sound.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'Which word has the same ''th'' sound as health?', 'That', 'These', 'Thick', 'Then', 'Thick', 'Voiceless th sound.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'Which word has the same ''th'' sound as father?', 'Thin', 'Math', 'Thank', 'Than', 'Than', 'Voiced th sound.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'Which word has the same ''th'' sound as then?', 'Weather', 'Thin', 'Thank', 'Math', 'Weather', 'Voiced th sound.', 'Medium'),
(2, 'Which word has the same ''th'' sound as there?', 'Thin', 'Thank', 'These', 'Math', 'These', 'Voiced th sound.', 'Medium');
INSERT INTO questionList (subjID, questionText, option1, option2, option3, option4, correctAnswer, correctExplanation, difficulty) VALUES
(2, '''Mother told me to fetch one of the ______. '' What is the plural form of trolley?', 'trolleys', 'trollies', 'trolleyes', 'trollys', 'trolleys', 'If a word ends in -ey, we just add -s to make it plural.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''I was asked to help make ______. '' What is the plural form of jelly?', 'jellys', 'jellies', 'jelleys', 'jellis', 'jellies', 'For words ending in a consonant + y, change the ''y'' to ''ies''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''My aunt is teaching me how to make ______. '' What is the plural form of stitch?', 'stitchs', 'stichtes', 'stitches', 'stitchies', 'stitches', 'Words ending in -ch need -es to become plural.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''My history teacher is teaching us about ______. '' What is the plural form of dynasty?', 'dynastys', 'dynastyes', 'dynasties', 'dynastis', 'dynasties', 'Change the ''y'' to ''ies'' because dynasty ends in a consonant + y.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''I am playing this game, and I have 2 ______ left.'' What is the plural form of life?', 'lifes', 'livees', 'lives', 'lifves', 'lives', 'For many words ending in -fe, we change -fe to -ves.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''You have to be careful when climbing a tree; the ______ might break.'' What is the plural form of branch?', 'branchs', 'branches', 'branchies', 'branchys', 'branches', 'Words ending in -ch, like branch, add -es for the plural form.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''My favorite birds are blue ______!'' What is the plural form of jay?', 'jays', 'jaies', 'jayes', 'jaysies', 'jays', 'When a word ends in a vowel + y (like -ay), just add -s.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''I am watching my dad paint the ______.'' What is the plural form of roof?', 'rooves', 'roofs', 'roofes', 'roofies', 'roofs', 'Unlike ''leaf'', the word ''roof'' just adds an -s to become plural.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Shhh! I am playing hide and seek; don''t tell them I am hiding in the ______.'' What is the plural of bush?', 'bushs', 'bushes', 'citizen', 'bushis', 'bushes', 'Words ending in -sh add -es to become plural.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''I love it when our teacher reads _____ to us.'' What is the plural form of fable?', 'fables', 'fablees', 'fablis', 'fableses', 'fables', 'For words ending in -e, simply add -s.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''I wanted to join the contest but there aren''t any ______ left.'' What is the plural form of entry?', 'entrys', 'entries', 'entryes', 'entris', 'entries', 'The ''y'' in entry changes to ''ies'' because it follows a consonant.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''I don''t want to grow old! I don''t even know how to file ______.'' What is the plural form of tax?', 'taxs', 'taxis', 'taxes', 'taxies', 'taxes', 'Words ending in -x need -es to become plural.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Look at all those tall ______ at the zoo!'' What is the plural form of giraffe?', 'giraffes', 'giraffies', 'giraffve', 'giraffs', 'giraffes', 'To make giraffe plural, we simply add -s.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''I am going with my mom to buy some ______.'' What is the plural form of grocery?', 'grocerys', 'groceries', 'groceriesies', 'groceryes', 'groceries', 'Change the ''y'' to ''ies'' to make grocery plural.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''A ___oriented man took books from the store without paying.'' What is the correct prefix to show he was not honest?', 'mis-', 'dis-', 'un-', 're-', 'dis-', 'Disoriented means confused, but in this context, ''dishonest'' is implied by ''dis-''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''He ___understood what the salesclerk told him about the sale.'' What is the correct prefix?', 'un-', 'dis-', 're-', 'mis-', 'mis-', 'Misunderstood means to understand something incorrectly.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''The salesclerk became ___courteous when the man walked away.'' What is the correct prefix?', 'dis-', 'in-', 'im-', 're-', 'dis-', 'Discourteous is the opposite of being polite or courteous.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''The store owner also became ___easy about the situation.'' What is the correct prefix?', 'dis-', 'un-', 'in-', 'mis-', 'un-', 'Uneasy means feeling worried or uncomfortable.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''He had to settle the ___agreement between the man and the salesclerk.'' What is the correct prefix?', 're-', 'un-', 'dis-', 'mis-', 'dis-', 'A disagreement happens when people do not agree.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''The store owner was ___partial and understanding.'' What is the correct prefix?', 'un-', 'im-', 'dis-', 're-', 'im-', 'Impartial means being fair and not taking sides.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''He had the courage to __write his essay when given a second chance.'' What is the correct prefix?', 're-', 'pre-', 'dis-', 'un-', 're-', 'Rewrite means to write something again.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''The father ___made the dough so he could bake with his daughter later.'' What is the correct prefix?', 're-', 'pre-', 'mis-', 'dis-', 'pre-', 'Premade means something was made ahead of time.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Do you know Manny Pacquiao? The famous box__?'' Which suffix completes the word for the person?', 'boxful', 'boxer', 'boxness', 'boxor', 'boxer', 'The suffix -er is added to an action to describe the person who does it.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''The kids at the park were very play___.'' What is the correct suffix?', 'player', 'playness', 'playful', 'playor', 'playful', 'Playful means full of play or fun.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''The children thanked the neighbor''s kind___ for returning the ball.'' What is the correct suffix?', 'kindly', 'kindness', 'kinder', 'kindful', 'kindness', 'Kindness is the state or quality of being kind.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''He asked the bank___ how to make a deposit.'' Which suffix completes the word for the person?', 'banker', 'bankor', 'bankness', 'bankful', 'banker', 'A banker is a person who works in a bank.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''The scientist asked the young invent___ about his project.'' Which suffix completes the word for the person?', 'inventer', 'inventor', 'inventness', 'inventful', 'inventor', 'An inventor is a person who creates or invents things.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''I dreaded the day of the spelling contest because I was not prepared.'' What does dreaded mean?', 'liked', 'feared', 'ignored', 'forgot', 'feared', 'To dread something means to be very afraid of it.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''One of the contestants felt embarrassed when he mispronounced a word.'' What does embarrassed mean?', 'proud', 'happy', 'ashamed', 'angry', 'ashamed', 'To feel embarrassed is to feel self-conscious or ashamed.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Another contestant was not in a good mood because she was sick.'' What does mood mean?', 'health', 'spirit', 'voice', 'answer', 'spirit', 'Mood refers to a person''s state of mind or spirit.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''The audience was indifferent to the decision.'' In this sentence, what does indifferent mean?', 'angry', 'uninterested', 'excited', 'happy', 'uninterested', 'Indifferent means having no particular interest or sympathy.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Our school is a member of a sports league in Quezon City.'' What is a league?', 'building', 'association', 'contest', 'classroom', 'association', 'A league is a group or association of teams that compete against each other.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''The campaign was advertised for a long time.'' What does advertised mean?', 'kept secret', 'always announced', 'forgotten', 'stopped', 'always announced', 'To advertise is to announce or praise something publicly.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Violators of the campaign disappointed the school officials.'' What does disappointed mean?', 'helped', 'failed', 'pleased', 'joined', 'failed', 'To disappoint means to fail to fulfill someone''s hopes or expectations.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''The sprinter recorded a fast 100-meter run.'' What is a sprinter?', 'a fast runner', 'a slow walker', 'a judge', 'a teacher', 'a fast runner', 'A sprinter is an athlete who runs short distances at top speed.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''They watched the Kite Flying Festival.'' What is the subject pronoun in this sentence?', 'They', 'watched', 'Kite', 'Festival', 'They', '''They'' is the subject pronoun because it is the group doing the action.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''She took pictures of the kites.'' What is the subject pronoun in this sentence?', 'pictures', 'kites', 'She', 'took', 'She', '''She'' is the subject pronoun replacing the name of a girl.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''He saw his friend watch the festival too.'' What is the subject pronoun?', 'festival', 'friend', 'He', 'saw', 'He', '''He'' is the subject pronoun acting as the subject of the sentence.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''We cheered for all the contestants.'' What is the subject pronoun?', 'cheered', 'contestants', 'all', 'We', 'We', '''We'' is the subject pronoun representing the speaker and others.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''You can join us for a snack.'' What is the subject pronoun?', 'join', 'us', 'snack', 'You', 'You', '''You'' is the subject pronoun being spoken to directly.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''I was tired but happy to participate.'' What is the subject pronoun?', 'tired', 'I', 'participate', 'happy', 'I', '''I'' is the subject pronoun referring to the person speaking.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''It was a real unforgettable experience.'' What is the subject pronoun?', 'experience', 'unforgettable', 'It', 'was', 'It', '''It'' is the subject pronoun referring to the event.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''You and I should consider participating again.'' What is the subject pronoun?', 'participating', 'You and I', 'again', 'consider', 'You and I', '''You and I'' is a compound subject pronoun.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Mr. Cruz tells us to prepare for the competition.'' What is the object pronoun?', 'Mr. Cruz', 'prepare', 'us', 'competition', 'us', '''Us'' is the object pronoun because it receives the action of being told.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''He requested me to be present at the practice.'' What is the object pronoun?', 'requested', 'me', 'practice', 'present', 'me', '''Me'' is the object pronoun following the verb ''requested''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''He asked them to run three times around the field.'' What is the object pronoun?', 'run', 'them', 'field', 'asked', 'them', '''Them'' is the object pronoun receiving the action of being asked.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''The trainer taught them the proper pacing.'' What is the object pronoun?', 'trainer', 'pacing', 'them', 'taught', 'them', '''Them'' is the object pronoun in this sentence.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Proper pacing will help you last the entire game.'' What is the object pronoun?', 'pacing', 'help', 'you', 'game', 'you', '''You'' is the object pronoun receiving the help.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''I met with the coach and reminded him of the game.'' What is the object pronoun?', 'met', 'coach', 'him', 'reminded', 'him', '''Him'' is the object pronoun referring to the coach.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''The coach told me to keep my cool.'' What is the object pronoun?', 'coach', 'told', 'me', 'cool', 'me', '''Me'' is the object pronoun in this sentence.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''I also went to see our principal, and I told her about the team.'' What is the object pronoun?', 'I', 'her', 'team', 'principal', 'her', '''Her'' is the object pronoun because she is the one receiving the information.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''October 24 is a day to remember. ______ is United Nations Day.'' What is the right pronoun for October 24?', 'She', 'It', 'They', 'He', 'It', 'We use ''it'' to replace a date or a specific day.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Children in the school usually have a program in which ______ wear costumes.'' What is the right pronoun for children?', 'he', 'we', 'they', 'it', 'they', '''They'' is the plural pronoun used to replace ''children''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Michelle, your Halloween costume is ready,'' Mother told ______. What is the right pronoun for Michelle?', 'him', 'her', 'it', 'me', 'her', '''Her'' is the object pronoun used for a girl or woman.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Mother had sewn my costume last month, so ______ does not need to buy one.'' What is the right pronoun for Mother?', 'she', 'he', 'it', 'they', 'she', '''She'' is the subject pronoun used to replace ''Mother''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Jane and I had a part in the program; ______ performed a dance.'' What is the right pronoun for Jane and I?', 'They', 'We', 'You', 'She', 'We', '''We'' is the pronoun used when the speaker is included with another person.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Mang Bert has many stores. This one near our house is ____.'' What is the right possessive pronoun?', 'him', 'his', 'he', 'hers', 'his', '''His'' shows that the store belongs to Mang Bert.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''He treats _____ customers fairly.'' What is the right possessive pronoun?', 'his', 'her', 'our', 'their', 'his', '''His'' is the possessive adjective used for a man.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''We buy ____ personal needs from the store.'' What is the right possessive pronoun?', 'your', 'their', 'our', 'my', 'our', '''Our'' matches the subject ''we''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Do you know ____ way to the store?'' What is the right possessive pronoun?', 'my', 'your', 'his', 'her', 'your', '''Your'' is the possessive adjective that matches the person being spoken to.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''This umbrella is from the store. Is it ____?'' What is the right possessive pronoun?', 'your', 'yours', 'my', 'me', 'yours', '''Yours'' is used as a possessive pronoun at the end of the sentence.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Tita Marie has a new restaurant. Is that ____ restaurant beside the store?'' What is the right possessive pronoun?', 'his', 'her', 'hers', 'their', 'her', '''Her'' is the possessive adjective used for Tita Marie.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Yes, the restaurant beside Mang Bert''s store is ____.'' What is the right possessive pronoun?', 'her', 'his', 'hers', 'mine', 'hers', '''Hers'' is the possessive pronoun used to show it belongs to her.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Let us have ____ lunch there.'' What is the right possessive pronoun?', 'our', 'their', 'my', 'your', 'our', '''Our'' is used because ''us'' includes the speaker.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''I wonder where ____ weird sounds came from?'' (The sounds are far away) What is the right demonstrative?', 'this', 'that', 'these', 'those', 'those', 'Use ''those'' for many things that are far away.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''____ sound seems to come from _____ santol tree over there.'' What are the right demonstratives?', 'this and this', 'that and that', 'these and those', 'this and that', 'that and that', 'Both the sound and the tree are far away (''over there''), so we use ''that''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''I think the cicadas on ____ tree by me is making ____ weird sound.'' What are the right demonstratives?', 'this and that', 'that and this', 'these and those', 'this and this', 'this and that', 'The tree is close (''by me''), but the sound feels more distant.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Let us go near ____ santol tree.'' What is the right demonstrative?', 'this', 'that', 'these', 'those', 'that', 'We use ''that'' because they are moving toward a tree that is currently further away.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''But the sound suddenly stopped. What does ____ mean?'' What is the right demonstrative?', 'this', 'that', 'these', 'those', 'that', '''That'' is often used to refer to a situation that just happened.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''I don''t know, but ____ raindrops are becoming bigger and bigger.'' (Rain is falling on them) What is the right demonstrative?', 'this', 'that', 'these', 'those', 'these', 'Use ''these'' for many things that are close or touching you.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''____ cicadas might have flown away because of the rain.'' (The speaker is looking at the far trees) What is the right demonstrative?', 'this', 'that', 'these', 'those', 'those', 'Use ''those'' for plural things that are far away.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Are ____ insects afraid of water?'' (Referring to the ones far away) What is the right demonstrative?', 'this', 'that', 'these', 'those', 'those', '''Those'' is used for plural objects at a distance.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''The books are on my table. _____ are my books.'' What is the right demonstrative?', 'That', 'This', 'These', 'Those', 'These', 'Since the books are on the table right in front of the speaker, we use ''these''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''The coat I am wearing was my mother''s gift. ____ is my favorite coat.'' What is the right demonstrative?', 'This', 'That', 'These', 'Those', 'This', 'Use ''this'' for one thing you are wearing or holding.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Father wears his sunglasses. _____ are his sunglasses.'' What is the right demonstrative?', 'This', 'That', 'These', 'Those', 'Those', 'If the sunglasses are on his face (and the speaker is looking at him), ''those'' is used to point them out.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Look up at the sky. _____ is my brother''s kite.'' What is the right demonstrative?', 'This', 'That', 'These', 'Those', 'That', 'Use ''that'' for one thing far away in the sky.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Can you see the white house over there? _____ is my friend''s house.'' What is the right demonstrative?', 'This', 'That', 'These', 'Those', 'That', '''That'' is used to point to a single building in the distance.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''The children _____ the street.'' Which verb correctly completes the sentence?', 'sweeps', 'sweep', 'sweeping', 'swept', 'sweep', '''Children'' is plural, so we use the base form of the verb ''sweep''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''The people _____ the canals clean.'' Which verb correctly completes the sentence?', 'keeps', 'keeping', 'keep', 'kept', 'keep', '''People'' is plural, so it takes the plural verb ''keep''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''My friends _____ the walls.'' Which verb correctly completes the sentence?', 'scrubs', 'scrub', 'scrubbing', 'scrubbed', 'scrub', '''Friends'' is a plural subject, so it needs the verb ''scrub''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''The residents _____ their community clean.'' Which verb correctly completes the sentence?', 'makes', 'make', 'making', 'made', 'make', 'Plural subjects like ''residents'' use ''make''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''The city mayor _____ the barangay weekly.'' Which verb correctly completes the sentence?', 'visits', 'visit', 'visiting', 'visited', 'visits', '''Mayor'' is a singular subject, so we add -s to the verb: ''visits''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''He _____ to know if the town is clean.'' Which verb correctly completes the sentence?', 'want', 'wants', 'wanting', 'wanted', 'wants', 'Singular subjects like ''He'' require the verb to end in -s.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Some doctors and nurses _____ to the people.'' Which verb correctly completes the sentence?', 'talks', 'talk', 'talking', 'talked', 'talk', 'Since there is more than one person (doctors and nurses), we use ''talk''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''They _____ the people about the importance of cleanliness.'' Which verb correctly completes the sentence?', 'tells', 'telling', 'tell', 'told', 'tell', '''They'' is a plural pronoun, so it uses the verb ''tell''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Parent volunteers also _____ maintain cleanliness and orderliness.'' Which verb fits correctly?', 'helps', 'help', 'helping', 'helped', 'help', '''Volunteers'' is plural, so we use the base form ''help''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''My teacher _____ my classmates to join the cleanliness program.'' Which verb fits correctly?', 'encourage', 'encourages', 'encouraging', 'encouraged', 'encourages', '''Teacher'' is singular, so we add -s to the verb.', 'Hard'),
(2, 'Which word has the same ''-ough'' sound as ''though''?', 'tough', 'dough', 'fought', 'rough', 'dough', '''Though'' and ''dough'' both have a long ''o'' sound.', 'Hard'),
(2, 'Which word has the same ''-ough'' sound as ''fought''?', 'bought', 'dough', 'though', 'through', 'bought', '''Fought'' and ''bought'' both have the ''aw'' sound.', 'Hard'),
(2, 'Which word has the same ''-ough'' sound as ''rough''?', 'though', 'thought', 'tough', 'bough', 'tough', '''Rough'' and ''tough'' both end with a ''uff'' sound.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''(We are) _____ going to Cebu to visit my lolo and lola.'' What is the correct contraction?', 'Were', 'We''re', 'We''r', 'Where', 'We''re', '''We''re'' is the short way to write ''we are''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''I (cannot) _____ wait to see them.'' What is the correct contraction?', 'cant''', 'can''t', 'ca''nt', 'cann', 'can''t', '''Can''t'' is the contraction for ''cannot''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''(He is) _____ taking us to the farm.'' What is the correct contraction?', 'He''s', 'His', 'Hes''', 'Heis', 'He''s', '''He''s'' is the short way to write ''he is''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''(She is) _____ planning to go to the market today.'' What is the correct contraction?', 'Shes', 'She''s', 'Shes''', 'Sheis', 'She''s', '''She''s'' is the contraction for ''she is''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''(I am) _____ going to buy something for them.'' What is the correct contraction?', 'Im', 'I''am', 'I''m', 'I-m', 'I''m', '''I''m'' is the contraction for ''I am''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''I know (they are) _____ eagerly waiting for us.'' What is the correct contraction?', 'their', 'there', 'they''re', 'theyre', 'they''re', '''They''re'' is the short way to write ''they are''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Now, I (could not) _____ sleep.'' What is the correct contraction?', 'couldnt', 'could''nt', 'couldn''t', 'couldn', 'couldn''t', '''Couldn''t'' is the contraction for ''could not''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''I know (you are) _____ very excited, but you should sleep.'' What is the correct contraction?', 'your', 'you''re', 'youre', 'yore', 'you''re', '''You''re'' is the contraction for ''you are''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Yes mother, (I will) _____ do it.'' What is the correct contraction?', 'I''l', 'I''ll', 'Ill', 'I-ll', 'I''ll', '''I''ll'' is the short way to write ''I will''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''It (was not) _____ easy, though, to close my eyes.'' What is the correct contraction?', 'wasnt', 'was''nt', 'wasn''t', 'wasn', 'wasn''t', '''Wasn''t'' is the contraction for ''was not''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Everyday last month, Miguel _____ two trips to the deep well.'' What is the past tense of make?', 'maked', 'makes', 'made', 'making', 'made', '''Made'' is the irregular past tense form of ''make''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''His mother _____ that Miguel was learning a valuable lesson.'' What is the past tense of know?', 'knowed', 'knew', 'known', 'knows', 'knew', '''Knew'' is the irregular past tense of ''know''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''At first, Miguel _____ it very difficult.'' What is the past tense of find?', 'finded', 'found', 'founds', 'finding', 'found', '''Found'' is the past tense of ''find''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''As the days passed, he _____ used to it.'' What is the past tense of get?', 'getted', 'gotten', 'got', 'gets', 'got', 'The past tense of ''get'' is ''got''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Soon, Miguel''s hard work _____ off.'' What is the past tense of pay?', 'payed', 'paid', 'pays', 'paying', 'paid', 'The correct spelling for the past tense of ''pay'' is ''paid''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''His plants _____ healthier and prettier.'' What is the past tense of grow?', 'growed', 'grew', 'grown', 'grows', 'grew', '''Grew'' is the past tense of the verb ''grow''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''The neighbors _____ how the plants prospered.'' What is the past tense of see?', 'seed', 'saw', 'seen', 'sees', 'saw', '''Saw'' is the past tense of the verb ''see''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''On the last day, Miguel _____ up early.'' What is the past tense of wake?', 'waked', 'woke', 'woken', 'wakes', 'woke', '''Woke'' is the past tense of ''wake''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''With his family, he hurriedly _____ to the plaza.'' What is the past tense of go?', 'goed', 'gone', 'went', 'goes', 'went', '''Went'' is the irregular past tense of ''go''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''It was announced that Miguel _____ the contest.'' What is the past tense of win?', 'winned', 'won', 'wons', 'winning', 'won', 'The past tense of ''win'' is ''won''.', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Cyril carried three ______ books.'' What is the right order of adjectives?', 'thick, green, big', 'green, big, thick', 'big, thick, green', 'big, green, thick', 'big, thick, green', 'The order should be Size (big), then Shape/Thickness (thick), then Color (green).', 'Hard'),
(2, '''He put them in a ______ backpack.'' What is the right order of adjectives?', 'blue, canvas, medium-sized', 'medium-sized, blue, canvas', 'canvas, blue, medium-sized', 'blue, medium-sized, canvas', 'medium-sized, blue, canvas', 'The order is Size (medium-sized), Color (blue), then Material (canvas).', 'Hard'),
(2, '''He got the backpack from a ______ cabinet.'' What is the right order of adjectives?', 'steel, tall, gray', 'tall, gray, steel', 'gray, tall, steel', 'tall, steel, gray', 'tall, gray, steel', 'The order is Size (tall), Color (gray), then Material (steel).', 'Hard'),
(2, '''Cyril rode in a ______ car.'' What is the right order of adjectives?', 'white, lovely, modern', 'modern, lovely, white', 'lovely, modern, white', 'lovely, white, modern', 'lovely, modern, white', 'The order is Opinion (lovely), Age (modern), then Color (white).', 'Hard'),
(2, 'What is the abbreviated form of ''Mister Reyes''?', 'Mtr. Reyes', 'Mr. Reyes', 'Mr Reyes.', 'Mist. Reyes', 'Mr. Reyes', '''Mr.'' is the standard abbreviation for ''Mister''.', 'Hard'),
(2, 'What is the abbreviated form of ''Aguinaldo Street''?', 'Aguinaldo Str.', 'Aguinaldo St.', 'Aguinaldo St', 'Aguinaldo Steet.', 'Aguinaldo St.', '''St.'' is the abbreviation for ''Street''.', 'Hard'),
(2, 'What is the abbreviated form of ''Pearl Building''?', 'Pearl Bld.', 'Pearl Blg.', 'Pearl Bldg.', 'Pearl Build.', 'Pearl Bldg.', '''Bldg.'' is the standard abbreviation for ''Building''.', 'Hard'),
(2, 'What is the abbreviated form of ''Tandang Sora Avenue''?', 'Tandang Sora Av.', 'Tandang Sora Ave.', 'Tandang Sora Avn.', 'Tandang Sora Aven.', 'Tandang Sora Ave.', '''Ave.'' is the abbreviation for ''Avenue''.', 'Hard'),
(2, 'What is the abbreviated form of ''Captain Ramos''?', 'Cpt. Ramos', 'Cap. Ramos', 'Capt. Ramos', 'Cptn. Ramos', 'Capt. Ramos', '''Capt.'' is the standard abbreviation for ''Captain''.', 'Hard');
 INSERT INTO questionList (subjID, questionText, option1, option2, option3, option4, correctAnswer, correctExplanation, difficulty) VALUES
(3, 'Sandpaper and Ampalaya (bitter gourd) both feel bumpy. They have the same _____.', 'Size', 'Color', 'Texture', 'Taste', 'Texture', 'Texture is how something feels when you touch it.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'A paperclip and a safety pin are both very small. They have the same ______.', 'Color', 'Size', 'Shape', 'Taste', 'Size', 'Both of these items are small in size.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'An apple and a drop of blood are both red. They have the same _____.', 'Shape', 'Taste', 'Size', 'Color', 'Color', 'They are both the same color (red).', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Tamarind and green mangoes are both sour. They have the same _____.', 'Smell', 'Taste', 'Size', 'Color', 'Taste', 'Both of these fruits taste sour.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Perfume smells nice, but garbage smells bad. They have different _____.', 'Odors', 'Shapes', 'Sizes', 'Colors', 'Odors', 'Odor is another word for smell.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'A bed and a door are both shaped like a rectangle. They have the same _____.', 'Color', 'Shape', 'Weight', 'Taste', 'Shape', 'Both items have a rectangular shape.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'A candy cane and a lollipop are both sweet. They have the same _____.', 'Shape', 'Size', 'Taste', 'Color', 'Taste', 'Candy is sweet to eat.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'A tire and a coin are both round. They have the same _____.', 'Texture', 'Weight', 'Shape', 'Color', 'Shape', 'Both are shaped like a circle.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What is something that is yellow and tastes sweet?', 'Grape', 'Banana', 'Lime', 'Leaf', 'Banana', 'A banana is a yellow fruit that tastes sweet.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What is something that is big and heavy?', 'A leaf', 'A log', 'A feather', 'A pencil', 'A log', 'A large log is very heavy to lift.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What is something that is green and small?', 'A pea', 'An elephant', 'A bus', 'A cloud', 'A pea', 'A pea is a tiny green vegetable.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What is something light and soft?', 'A rock', 'A feather', 'A brick', 'A coin', 'A feather', 'Feathers are very soft and do not weigh much.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What is something hard and thin?', 'A pillow', 'A metal stick', 'A marshmallow', 'A cloud', 'A metal stick', 'Metal is hard, and a stick can be very thin.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'A shoe is something you can hold. It is a _____.', 'Gas', 'Liquid', 'Solid', 'Cloud', 'Solid', 'A shoe has its own shape, so it is a solid.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'An electric fan is a machine. It is a _____.', 'Liquid', 'Gas', 'Solid', 'Water', 'Solid', 'Machines like fans are made of solid parts.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'A bottle of perfume is filled with _____.', 'Solid', 'Liquid', 'Gas', 'Ice', 'Liquid', 'The perfume inside the bottle is a wet liquid.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'A cup of water is a ____.', 'Solid', 'Liquid', 'Gas', 'Hard', 'Liquid', 'Water is a liquid that you can pour.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Smoke from a campfire rises into the air. It is a _____.', 'Solid', 'Liquid', 'Gas', 'Ice', 'Gas', 'Smoke is a gas that floats in the air.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'A river is made of flowing water. It is a ____.', 'Solid', 'Gas', 'Liquid', 'Rock', 'Liquid', 'Rivers are made of liquid water.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Air inside a balloon is a _____.', 'Solid', 'Liquid', 'Gas', 'Food', 'Gas', 'Air is a gas that fills up the balloon.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Nuts are crunchy and hard. They are _____.', 'Liquids', 'Gases', 'Solids', 'Water', 'Solids', 'Nuts are solid food.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What is the shape of a piece of notebook paper?', 'Circle', 'Triangle', 'Rectangle', 'Star', 'Rectangle', 'Notebook paper has four sides and is a rectangle.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What is the color of a piece of notebook paper?', 'Blue', 'White', 'Green', 'Red', 'White', 'Most notebook paper is white so we can see our writing.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What is the texture of a piece of notebook paper?', 'Bumpy', 'Sharp', 'Smooth', 'Sticky', 'Smooth', 'Notebook paper feels smooth when you touch it.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'If you put red dye into a glass of water, the water will change its what?', 'Shape', 'Color', 'Size', 'Sound', 'Color', 'The red dye turns the clear water into red water.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'If you cut a long string into many small pieces, the string changes its what?', 'Size', 'Smell', 'Taste', 'Color', 'Size', 'Cutting it makes the pieces smaller in size.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'If you mix a spoonful of sweet honey into water, the water changes its what?', 'Color', 'Shape', 'Taste', 'Size', 'Taste', 'The honey makes the water taste sweet.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'If you blow air into a balloon, the balloon will change its what?', 'Taste', 'Size', 'Color', 'Smell', 'Size', 'The air makes the balloon get bigger in size.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'If you spray perfume into the air, the room will change its what?', 'Shape', 'Smell', 'Size', 'Color', 'Smell', 'Perfume adds a nice scent or smell to the room.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What animal makes a "Roar!" sound?', 'Mouse', 'Sheep', 'Lion', 'Rabbit', 'Lion', 'Lions are famous for their loud roar.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What animal makes a "Mehhh!" sound?', 'Dog', 'Goat', 'Cat', 'Bird', 'Goat', 'A goat makes a bleating sound like ''mehhh''.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What animal makes a "Meow!" sound?', 'Cow', 'Pig', 'Cat', 'Dog', 'Cat', 'Cats say meow when they want attention.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What animal makes a "Chirp!" sound?', 'Bird', 'Lion', 'Snake', 'Horse', 'Bird', 'Little birds chirp in the trees.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What animal makes a "Moooo!" sound?', 'Goat', 'Cow', 'Duck', 'Chicken', 'Cow', 'Cows make a loud moo sound.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What animal makes a "Woof!" sound?', 'Dog', 'Cat', 'Fish', 'Bird', 'Dog', 'Dogs bark by saying woof or arf.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Which of these has a pleasant (nice) sound?', 'A loud siren', 'A lullaby', 'A car horn', 'A vacuum', 'A lullaby', 'A lullaby is a soft, pretty song for babies.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Which of these has a pleasant (nice) sound?', 'Fireworks', 'A door slamming', 'Piano music', 'A dog growling', 'Piano music', 'Piano music is usually very relaxing and nice to hear.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Which of these has a pleasant (nice) sound?', 'A violin', 'A whistle', 'A shout', 'A crash', 'A violin', 'A violin makes beautiful music.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Which of these has an unpleasant (loud/scary) sound?', 'A bell', 'Fireworks', 'A bird', 'A whisper', 'Fireworks', 'Fireworks make very loud, booming sounds.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Which of these has an unpleasant (scary) sound?', 'A piano', 'A siren', 'A laugh', 'A cat purring', 'A siren', 'Sirens are very loud to warn people of danger.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'The topmost part of your body where your hair grows is your _____.', 'Foot', 'Head', 'Arm', 'Leg', 'Head', 'Your head is at the very top of your body.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Your hands, arms, and fingers are called your _____.', 'Head', 'Chest', 'Limbs', 'Stomach', 'Limbs', 'Limbs are the parts of your body that move, like arms and legs.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Most of your important organs (like your heart) are inside your _____.', 'Hair', 'Nails', 'Body', 'Limbs', 'Body', 'Your main body (torso) holds your important organs.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Red, blue, yellow, high or low. I can see them all! What body part is used?', 'Nose', 'Eyes', 'Ears', 'Hands', 'Eyes', 'We use our eyes to see colors and things around us.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Soft sound, loud sound, nice sound, or scary sound. I hear them all! What body part is used?', 'Ears', 'Tongue', 'Eyes', 'Feet', 'Ears', 'We use our ears to listen to sounds.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Salty or bitter, sweet or spicy. I can tell how my food is! What body part is used?', 'Nose', 'Tongue', 'Elbow', 'Knee', 'Tongue', 'Your tongue helps you taste your food.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Mm! Mother is baking in the oven. I know because my ____ tells me! What body part is used?', 'Eyes', 'Ears', 'Nose', 'Teeth', 'Nose', 'Your nose helps you smell yummy food cooking.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Which of these does a monkey have?', 'Wings', 'Horns', 'Tail', 'Trunk', 'Tail', 'Monkeys use their tails to help them climb trees.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Which of these does a cow have?', 'Horns', 'Feathers', 'Gills', 'Shell', 'Horns', 'Many cows have horns on top of their heads.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Which of these does an octopus have?', 'Wings', 'Horns', 'Tentacles', 'Shell', 'Tentacles', 'Octopuses have eight long arms called tentacles.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Which of these does an elephant have?', 'Feathers', 'Trunk', 'Gills', 'Scales', 'Trunk', 'An elephant uses its long trunk to breathe and grab food.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Which of these does an eagle have?', 'Claws', 'Fins', 'Horns', 'Tentacles', 'Claws', 'Eagles use their sharp claws to catch food.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Which of these does a giraffe have?', 'Short tail', 'Long neck', 'Small ears', 'Big trunk', 'Long neck', 'A giraffe has a very long neck to reach leaves high in trees.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'How long should a growing child sleep every night?', '2 hours', '5 hours', '10 hours', '20 hours', '10 hours', 'Children need about 10 hours of sleep to stay healthy and grow.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What kind of food is rice? (It gives you energy to run)', 'Go food', 'Grow food', 'Glow food', 'Sweet food', 'Go food', 'Go foods like rice give our bodies energy to move.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What kind of food is bread?', 'Glow food', 'Go food', 'Grow food', 'Sour food', 'Go food', 'Bread is a Go food because it gives us energy.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What kind of food is pasta?', 'Go food', 'Glow food', 'Grow food', 'Salty food', 'Go food', 'Pasta gives you the energy to ''Go'' and play!', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What kind of food are biscuits?', 'Grow food', 'Glow food', 'Go food', 'Spicy food', 'Go food', 'Biscuits are made of flour, which gives us energy.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What kind of food are carrots? (They make your skin and eyes healthy)', 'Go food', 'Grow food', 'Glow food', 'Meat food', 'Glow food', 'Glow foods like carrots keep our skin and eyes healthy.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What kind of food are apples?', 'Glow food', 'Go food', 'Grow food', 'Oily food', 'Glow food', 'Fruits like apples are Glow foods that prevent us from getting sick.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What kind of food are potatoes?', 'Grow food', 'Go food', 'Glow food', 'Soft food', 'Glow food', 'Potatoes are vegetables that help our bodies stay healthy.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What kind of food are strawberries?', 'Go food', 'Grow food', 'Glow food', 'Bitter food', 'Glow food', 'Strawberries are healthy fruits that belong to the Glow group.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What kind of food are eggs? (They help build your muscles)', 'Grow food', 'Go food', 'Glow food', 'Leafy food', 'Grow food', 'Grow foods like eggs help our muscles and bones get stronger.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What kind of food is chicken?', 'Go food', 'Glow food', 'Grow food', 'Fruit food', 'Grow food', 'Chicken is a protein that helps your body grow big.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What kind of food is milk?', 'Grow food', 'Go food', 'Glow food', 'Candy food', 'Grow food', 'Milk has calcium to help your bones grow.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What kind of food is fish?', 'Go food', 'Glow food', 'Grow food', 'Green food', 'Grow food', 'Fish is a healthy Grow food for your body.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What kind of food is chocolate?', 'Go food', 'Glow food', 'Sweet food', 'Grow food', 'Sweet food', 'Chocolate has a lot of sugar, so it is a sweet food.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What kind of food is candy?', 'Sweet food', 'Grow food', 'Glow food', 'Go food', 'Sweet food', 'Candy is a treat that tastes very sweet.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What kind of food is ice cream?', 'Glow food', 'Go food', 'Sweet food', 'Grow food', 'Sweet food', 'Ice cream is a cold and sweet dessert.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What is a form of energy that helps us see everything around us?', 'Sound', 'Light', 'Smell', 'Wind', 'Light', 'We need light to see colors and shapes.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What gives the most heat and light to the Earth?', 'A flashlight', 'A candle', 'The Sun', 'The Moon', 'The Sun', 'The Sun is a giant star that lights up our world.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'How does heat and light from the sun reach the Earth?', 'Walking', 'Radiation', 'A giant tube', 'The wind', 'Radiation', 'Radiation is how energy travels through space to reach us.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What force makes home appliances (like a TV or fridge) work?', 'Gravity', 'Electricity', 'Magnets', 'Wind', 'Electricity', 'Electricity flows through wires to power our homes.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What is a push or a pull that can make something move?', 'Force', 'Sound', 'Light', 'Color', 'Force', 'When you push or pull a toy, you are using force.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What uses heat energy to change things?', 'Sleeping', 'Running', 'Cooking', 'Drawing', 'Cooking', 'Cooking uses heat to make food ready to eat.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What can move objects made of steel or iron without touching them?', 'Water', 'Magnets', 'Air', 'Paper', 'Magnets', 'Magnets pull on certain metals like iron.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What is the force that makes things fall down to the ground?', 'Electricity', 'Gravity', 'Magnets', 'Light', 'Gravity', 'Gravity pulls everything toward the center of the Earth.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What forms of energy does the sun give us?', 'Only sound', 'Only smell', 'Both heat and light', 'Only electricity', 'Both heat and light', 'The sun makes the Earth warm and bright.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What is the biggest part of the Earth''s surface?', 'Trees', 'Water', 'Rocks', 'Cities', 'Water', 'Most of the Earth is covered by big oceans of water.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What is made up of the gases that surround the Earth?', 'Land', 'Air', 'Water', 'Fire', 'Air', 'Air is the invisible gas that we breathe.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What part of the Earth is made up of rocks and soil?', 'Ocean', 'Land', 'Sky', 'Clouds', 'Land', 'Land is the solid part of Earth that we walk on.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What is a high piece of land that can erupt with hot lava?', 'A hill', 'A volcano', 'A valley', 'A river', 'A volcano', 'Volcanoes are mountains that can blow out hot melted rock.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What is the biggest body of water on Earth?', 'A pond', 'A lake', 'The Ocean', 'A puddle', 'The Ocean', 'Oceans are huge areas of salty water.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What happens when harmful things make the environment dirty?', 'Cleaning', 'Pollution', 'Planting', 'Painting', 'Pollution', 'Pollution makes the air, water, or land unsafe.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'What is another word for moving air?', 'Rain', 'Dust', 'Wind', 'Snow', 'Wind', 'Wind is air that is traveling from one place to another.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Which of these shows that you care for the Earth?', 'Throwing trash in a river', 'Planting more trees', 'Leaving the lights on', 'Wasting water', 'Planting more trees', 'Trees help keep the air clean and give homes to animals.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'How can you describe the weather?', 'It never changes', 'It is always hot', 'It can change at any time', 'It is always rainy', 'It can change at any time', 'Weather can be sunny in the morning and rainy in the afternoon.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'Why can you not see the sun at night?', 'Because it turns off', 'Because it is behind the moon', 'It is shining on the other side of Earth', 'Because it goes to sleep', 'It is shining on the other side of Earth', 'The Earth spins, so the sun shines on the other side at night.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'The rain is pouring hard and there are very strong winds. What is the weather?', 'Sunny', 'Stormy', 'Fair', 'Hot', 'Stormy', 'A storm has lots of rain and very fast wind.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'The sun is being covered by many clouds. What is the weather?', 'Sunny', 'Cloudy', 'Windy', 'Clear', 'Cloudy', 'When clouds block the sun, we call it a cloudy day.', 'Easy'),
(3, 'The wind is blowing hard, but the sky is clear. What is the weather?', 'Rainy', 'Windy', 'Stormy', 'Snowy', 'Windy', 'A windy day is perfect for flying a kite!', 'Easy'),
(3, 'The clouds are dark and rain is falling down. What is the weather?', 'Sunny', 'Rainy', 'Windy', 'Dry', 'Rainy', 'Rainy weather happens when water falls from the clouds.', 'Easy');
INSERT INTO questionList (subjID, questionText, option1, option2, option3, option4, correctAnswer, correctExplanation, difficulty) VALUES
(3, 'Which is the heaviest?', 'A teddy bear', 'A chair', 'A pillow', 'A log', 'A log', 'A log weighs more than a teddy bear or a chair.', 'Medium'),
