INSERT INTO questionList (subjID, questionText, option1, option2, option3, option4, correctAnswer, correctExplanation, difficulty) VALUES
(3,'I am the only type of matter that does not ''shape-shift'' and keeps a fixed shape. What am I?','Solid','Liquid','Gas','Plasma','Solid','Solids have a definite shape and volume because their particles are packed closely together.','Hard'),
(3,'I am a ''shape-shifter'' that can expand to fill a big container or squeeze into a small one. What am I?','Solid','Liquid','Gas','Ice','Gas','Gases have no definite shape or volume; they fill whatever space is available.','Hard'),
(3,'Milk, coffee, and juice are all examples of me. No matter which you choose, what am I?','Solid','Liquid','Gas','Air','Liquid','Liquids have a definite volume but take the shape of their container.','Hard'),
(3,'I follow the shape of my container, but if you pour me into something too small, I will spill. What am I?','Solid','Liquid','Gas','Oxygen','Liquid','Liquids flow and take the shape of the container they occupy.','Hard'),
(3,'I move freely, and you can barely see or feel me. What am I?','Solid','Liquid','Gas','Water','Gas','Gas particles are very far apart and move rapidly in all directions.','Hard'),
(3,'If I am rectangular, you cannot make me fit into a small circular hole without breaking me. What am I?','Solid','Liquid','Gas','Steam','Solid','Solids resist changes to their shape.','Hard'),
(3,'The air you breathe is just like me. What am I?','Solid','Liquid','Gas','Honey','Gas','Air is a mixture of different gases like nitrogen and oxygen.','Hard'),
(3,'When you pop a balloon, you let me out into the room. What am I?','Solid','Liquid','Gas','Dust','Gas','The air trapped inside a balloon is in a gaseous state.','Hard'),
(3,'Your pencils and erasers are both examples of this state of matter. What am I?','Solid','Liquid','Gas','Plasma','Solid','Pencils and erasers are firm and keep their shape, making them solids.','Hard'),
(3,'My particles are far apart so I can flow, but they are not as far apart as a gas. What am I?','Solid','Liquid','Gas','Smoke','Liquid','Liquid particles have enough space to slide past each other, allowing them to flow.','Hard'),
(3,'What is the boiling point of water in Celsius?','0 degrees','50 degrees','100 degrees','212 degrees','100 degrees','At sea level, pure water boils and turns into steam at 100Â°C.','Hard'),
(3,'What is the freezing point of water in Celsius?','0 degrees','32 degrees','10 degrees','-10 degrees','0 degrees','Water turns from a liquid to a solid (ice) at 0Â°C.','Hard'),
(3,'When bright lights are switched on, we blink because this part helps the eye adjust and stay protected.','Iris','Eyelids','Pupil','Retina','Eyelids','Eyelids act as a protective shutter for the eye.','Hard'),
(3,'When we sweat, this part prevents the moisture from dripping straight into our eyes.','Eyelashes','Eyelids','Eyebrows','Sclera','Eyebrows','Eyebrows are shaped to divert sweat and rain away from the eye sockets.','Hard'),
(3,'Found at the edges of the eyelids, these prevent small dust particles from entering our eyes.','Eyebrows','Eyelashes','Pupil','Iris','Eyelashes','Eyelashes act as sensors and filters to keep debris out of the eye.','Hard'),
(3,'When a ball is thrown at you, your eyes automatically close because of this part.','Lens','Cornea','Eyelids','Optic Nerve','Eyelids','The blink reflex of the eyelids protects the eye from physical injury.','Hard'),
(3,'When we say someone has ''blue'' or ''brown'' eyes, which part are we talking about?','Pupil','Sclera','Iris','Cornea','Iris','The iris is the colored circular muscle that controls how much light enters the eye.','Hard'),
(3,'This part is the opening in the center of the iris that becomes larger when the light is dim.','Sclera','Lens','Pupil','Retina','Pupil','The pupil dilates (gets bigger) in the dark to let more light in so we can see.','Hard'),
(3,'This part sends nerve signals to the brain so it can tell what image we are looking at.','Optic nerve','Lens','Cornea','Iris','Optic nerve','The optic nerve carries electrical impulses from the retina to the brain.','Hard'),
(3,'What is the name of the tough, white outer layer that covers most of the eyeball?','Iris','Sclera','Pupil','Cornea','Sclera','The sclera is the ''white of the eye'' that provides protection and structure.','Hard'),
(3,'This part functions like a screen in a movie house where the image is projected.','Retina','Lens','Sclera','Pupil','Retina','The retina is the light-sensitive inner lining where images are formed.','Hard'),
(3,'This part acts like a camera lens that focuses light onto the retina to produce a clear image.','Cornea','Lens','Pupil','Iris','Lens','The lens changes shape to help us focus on objects at different distances.','Hard'),
(3,'This is the transparent outer ''window'' that helps the eye focus light as it enters.','Retina','Cornea','Pupil','Sclera','Cornea','The cornea is the clear front surface of the eye.','Hard'),
(3,'A classmate''s eyes are red and watering. What condition do they likely have?','A sty','Near-sightedness','Sore eyes (Conjunctivitis)','Cataracts','Sore eyes (Conjunctivitis)','Sore eyes, or pink eye, causes redness, itching, and watering.','Hard'),
(3,'You wake up with a painful red bump on the edge of your eyelid. What is it?','Sore eyes','A sty','Cataract','Near-sightedness','A sty','A sty is a small, painful lump on the eyelid caused by an infected gland.','Hard'),
(3,'If dust or a small object enters your eye at the park, what should you do first?','Rub your eyes hard','Wash your hands, then wash the eye with clean water','Use a sharp toothpick to get it out','Close your eyes and go to sleep','Wash your hands, then wash the eye with clean water','Washing with clean water is the safest way to remove debris without scratching the eye.','Hard'),
(3,'You feel nauseous reading far-away signs and they appear blurry. What should you do?','Buy sunglasses','Close one eye while reading','See a doctor for a vision test','Rub your eyes more often','See a doctor for a vision test','Blurry distant vision is a sign of being near-sighted and requires a professional check-up.','Hard'),
(3,'When you have sore eyes, which of these is a correct way to care for them?','Share your towel with a friend','Rub them with your fingers','Clean the eyelids gently with a clean cotton swab and water','Stare at the sun to dry them out','Clean the eyelids gently with a clean cotton swab and water','Keeping the area clean helps prevent further irritation and the spread of infection.','Hard'),
(3,'Which part of the ear holds the three tiny bones that vibrate to pass sound to the cochlea?','Outer ear','Middle ear','Inner ear','Ear canal','Middle ear','The middle ear contains the hammer, anvil, and stirrup bones.','Hard'),
(3,'Which part consists of the funnel-like structure (pinna) in charge of capturing sounds?','Inner ear','Middle ear','Outer ear','Cochlea','Outer ear','The outer ear collects sound waves and directs them into the ear canal.','Hard'),
(3,'In which part of the ear do nerve impulses form to be sent to the brain?','Outer ear','Ear canal','Inner ear','Eardrum','Inner ear','The cochlea in the inner ear turns vibrations into electrical signals for the brain.','Hard'),
(3,'Our ears are sometimes compared to a funnel because of how they capture sound. What is this part called?','Cochlea','Pinna','Eardrum','Semicircular canals','Pinna','The pinna is the visible part of the outer ear that funnels sound waves into the ear canal.','Hard'),
(3,'Which part of our ear vibrates first when sound waves enter the ear canal?','Hammer','Cochlea','Eardrum','Stirrup','Eardrum','The eardrum (tympanic membrane) is a thin membrane that vibrates when hit by sound waves.','Hard'),
(3,'Which part of our ears contains the tiny hair cells (cilia) that turn vibrations into nerve impulses?','Pinna','Eardrum','Cochlea','Auditory nerve','Cochlea','The cochlea is a snail-shaped structure where sound vibrations are converted into electrical signals.','Hard'),
(3,'If sound waves reach the eardrum but cannot reach the cochlea, which part is likely damaged?','Pinna','Hammer (Malleus)','Auditory nerve','Nostrils','Hammer (Malleus)','The hammer is one of the three tiny bones in the middle ear that must pass vibrations along.','Hard'),
(3,'If you keep losing your balance when you bend down or move, which part of your ear could be damaged?','Cochlea','Eardrum','Semicircular canals','Pinna','Semicircular canals','The semicircular canals in the inner ear are responsible for your sense of balance.','Hard'),
(3,'You hear sounds clearly, but you often identify them incorrectly. Which part is most likely having problems?','Eardrum','Pinna','Auditory nerve','Cochlea','Auditory nerve','The auditory nerve carries the signals to the brain for identification; if it is faulty, the brain gets the wrong message.','Hard'),
(3,'Which of the following parts of the nose are responsible for catching dirt and dust in the air we inhale?','Nostrils','Cilia and mucus','Nasal cavity','Olfactory nerve','Cilia and mucus','Cilia (tiny hairs) and mucus trap dust and germs to keep them out of your lungs.','Hard'),
(3,'Which part of the nose is the main space that leads back to the throat and allows air to reach the nerves?','Nostrils','Nasal cavity','Septum','Mucous membrane','Nasal cavity','The nasal cavity is the large air-filled space behind the nose.','Hard'),
(3,'If the air we inhale is not warmed or moistened to the right temperature, which part did not function correctly?','Nostrils','Cilia','Mucous membrane','Olfactory nerve','Mucous membrane','The mucous membrane warms and moistens the air before it goes deeper into the body.','Hard'),
(3,'Which part of the nose sends nerve signals so the brain can identify specific scents?','Nostrils','Olfactory nerve','Nasal cavity','Septum','Olfactory nerve','The olfactory nerve is the sensory nerve for the sense of smell.','Hard'),
(3,'Which part of the nose serves as the two main external passageways for air coming in and out?','Septum','Nostrils','Cilia','Olfactory bulb','Nostrils','Nostrils are the two openings at the front of the nose.','Hard'),
(3,'What kind of flavor does a typical berry-flavored candy have?','Sour','Sweet','Salty','Bitter','Sweet','Candy is primarily made of sugar, which tastes sweet.','Hard'),
(3,'What kind of flavor does a ripe mango have?','Bitter','Salty','Sweet','Sour','Sweet','As fruits like mangoes ripen, their starch turns into sugar, making them sweet.','Hard'),
(3,'What kind of flavor does a green (unripe) mango have?','Sweet','Sour','Salty','Bitter','Sour','Green mangoes contain high levels of acid, giving them a sharp sour taste.','Hard'),
(3,'What kind of flavor does vinegar have?','Sweet','Salty','Bitter','Sour','Sour','Vinegar contains acetic acid, which is detected by the sour taste buds.','Hard'),
(3,'What kind of flavor do potato chips typically have?','Salty','Sweet','Sour','Bitter','Salty','Potato chips are seasoned with salt (sodium chloride).','Hard'),
(3,'What kind of flavor does soy sauce have?','Sweet','Sour','Bitter','Salty','Salty','Soy sauce has a very high salt content, which dominates its flavor.','Hard'),
(3,'What kind of flavor does plain black coffee have?','Sweet','Salty','Bitter','Sour','Bitter','Coffee contains caffeine and other compounds that create a bitter taste.','Hard'),
(3,'What kind of flavor does ampalaya (bitter gourd) have?','Sweet','Salty','Bitter','Sour','Bitter','Ampalaya is well known for its distinct bitter flavor.','Hard'),
(3,'When it gets cold and the blood vessels in your skin react, which layer is primarily involved?','Epidermis','Dermis','Hypodermis','Hair','Dermis','The dermis contains blood vessels and nerves that respond to temperature changes.','Hard'),
(3,'When it is too hot because the sun''s rays are hitting your skin, which layer contains the sweat glands that help cool you down?','Epidermis','Dermis','Dead skin cells','Hair follicles','Dermis','Sweat glands are located in the dermis layer of the skin.','Hard'),
(3,'When you describe how smooth or rough an object is by touching it, which outermost layer is in direct contact with the object?','Dermis','Epidermis','Fat layer','Nerve endings','Epidermis','The epidermis is the top layer of skin that you use to touch things.','Hard'),
(3,'We get a lighter or darker complexion depending on the production of melanin. Which layer is this substance found in?','Dermis','Epidermis','Hypodermis','Sweat gland','Epidermis','Melanin is produced in the bottom part of the epidermis to protect the skin from UV rays.','Hard'),
(3,'The hair all over our body is fixed in its place. Which layer of the skin contains the hair follicles?','Epidermis','Dermis','Hypodermis','Melanin','Dermis','Hair follicles are rooted deep in the dermis layer.','Hard'),
(3,'If our skin is getting too dry because the oil-producing glands are not working, which layer is involved?','Epidermis','Dermis','Hypodermis','Pores','Dermis','The dermis contains sebaceous (oil) glands that keep the skin lubricated.','Hard'),
(3,'When we are in tremendous heat, we need to sweat to cool off. Which layer contains the sweat glands?','Hypodermis','Epidermis','Dermis','Nails','Dermis','Sweat glands are located in the dermis and release water to the surface to cool the body.','Hard'),
(3,'When we fall or hit something, we need a thick ''armor'' to protect our internal organs. Which thick layer acts as this cushion?','Epidermis','Dermis','Hair','Pores','Dermis','The dermis is much thicker than the epidermis and provides the skin''s strength and elasticity.','Hard'),
(3,'Which of the following is considered an unhealthy lifestyle choice?','Drinking 8 glasses of water','Eating junk food and soda for lunch','Eating fruits for dessert','Exercising daily','Eating junk food and soda for lunch','Junk food and soda are high in sugar and salt but low in nutrients.','Hard'),
(3,'Which of these habits is unhealthy?','Taking a bath every day','Washing hands before meals','Taking a shower only three times a week','Brushing teeth after every meal','Taking a shower only three times a week','Regular bathing is necessary to remove bacteria and stay healthy.','Hard'),
(3,'Which of these is a healthy lifestyle choice?','Eating vegetables every meal','Sleeping only 4 hours a night','Drinking soda instead of water','Skipping breakfast','Eating vegetables every meal','Vegetables provide essential vitamins and minerals for the body.','Hard'),
(3,'Which of these habits will help your body recover and grow?','Playing video games all night','Sleeping early every night','Eating candy for energy','Staying indoors all day','Sleeping early every night','The body repairs itself and grows during deep sleep.','Hard'),
(3,'Why is eating only one meal a day considered unhealthy?','It saves time','It helps you stay awake','It deprives the body of needed energy and nutrients','It makes you stronger','It deprives the body of needed energy and nutrients','The body needs consistent fuel throughout the day to function properly.','Hard'),
(3,'Which of these is an unhealthy hygiene practice?','Washing your face','Wearing clothes that haven''t been washed','Cutting your nails','Using clean socks','Wearing clothes that haven''t been washed','Dirty clothes can harbor bacteria and cause skin irritations or odors.','Hard'),
(3,'Which of these activities improves heart health?','Watching TV for 5 hours','Jogging three times a week','Sitting still all day','Eating salty snacks','Jogging three times a week','Regular aerobic exercise like jogging strengthens the heart and lungs.','Hard'),
(3,'Which of these is an unhealthy dental habit?','Flossing daily','Brushing your teeth once a day','Using fluoride toothpaste','Visiting a dentist','Brushing your teeth once a day','You should brush at least twice a day to prevent cavities and plaque.','Hard'),
(3,'What is a healthy way to stay hydrated?','Drinking a lot of water every day','Drinking coffee only','Drinking fruit juice with extra sugar','Drinking energy drinks','Drinking a lot of water every day','Water is the best fluid for keeping the body hydrated and healthy.','Hard'),
(3,'Why is sharing towels with all your siblings an unhealthy habit?','It saves water','It is a sign of friendship','It can spread skin diseases and germs','It makes the towel softer','It can spread skin diseases and germs','Sharing personal items like towels can transfer bacteria or fungal infections.','Hard'),
(3,'A bird uses its _____ to fly high up in the sky.','Beak','Wings','Claws','Tail','Wings','Wings provide the lift and thrust needed for birds to fly.','Hard'),
(3,'What is the main purpose of an aquatic animal''s fins?','Breathing','Swimming','Flying','Walking','Swimming','Fins help fish and other aquatic animals balance and move through the water.','Hard'),
(3,'Which part of an eagle is used to attack and capture its prey?','Beak','Wings','Claws (Talons)','Feathers','Claws (Talons)','Eagles use their sharp, strong talons to grab and hold onto their food.','Hard'),
(3,'Which part of an eagle is needed to spot food from a very high distance?','Eyes','Ears','Nostrils','Wings','Eyes','Eagles have very keen eyesight, allowing them to see small animals from miles away.','Hard'),
(3,'What kind of animals typically have wide and flat teeth for grinding plants?','Carnivores','Omnivores','Herbivores','Insects','Herbivores','Flat teeth are designed for chewing and grinding tough plant fibers.','Hard'),
(3,'Which part do terrestrial (land) animals commonly use to move around on the ground?','Fins','Gills','Legs','Wings','Legs','Legs provide support and movement for animals living on land.','Hard'),
(3,'Grasshoppers have hairs that detect air movement. This gives them a keen sense of _____.','Sight','Hearing','Touch','Smell','Touch','The hairs act as sensors that feel vibrations and changes in air pressure.','Hard'),
(3,'What kind of animals use wings to travel through the air?','Aquatic animals','Aerial animals','Terrestrial animals','Amphibians','Aerial animals','Aerial animals are those that spend much of their time flying.','Hard'),
(3,'Why do anteaters have long snouts and long, sticky tongues?','To breathe underwater','To reach ants and termites in small holes','To bite large animals','To make loud sounds','To reach ants and termites in small holes','Their specialized anatomy allows them to eat insects from deep inside mounds.','Hard'),
(3,'I have so many legs that you might give up counting as I move. What group do I belong to?','Amphibians','Arthropods','Mammals','Birds','Arthropods','Arthropods like centipedes and millipedes are known for having many legs.','Hard'),
(3,'I can live both on land and in water, especially as I get older. What am I?','Reptiles','Fish','Amphibians','Mollusks','Amphibians','Amphibians like frogs start life in water and can move to land as adults.','Hard'),
(3,'I was not hatched from an egg, and I drink milk from my mother. What am I?','Birds','Mammals','Reptiles','Fish','Mammals','Mammals give birth to live young and nurse them with milk.','Hard'),
(3,'I am covered in scales, and I use my fins and tail to help me swim. What am I?','Fish','Mollusks','Echinoderms','Birds','Fish','Fish are cold-blooded animals that live in water and breathe through gills.','Hard'),
(3,'I have a soft body and usually have one or two shells to protect me. What am I?','Arthropods','Mollusks','Amphibians','Mammals','Mollusks','Mollusks like snails and clams have soft bodies and often grow shells.','Hard'),
(3,'I usually have five matching parts and many tube-like feet. What am I?','Fish','Echinoderms','Reptiles','Birds','Echinoderms','Echinoderms, like starfish, often have radial symmetry and tube feet.','Hard'),
(3,'I can fly farther and higher because I am covered in light feathers. What am I?','Bats','Birds','Insects','Flying fish','Birds','Feathers are unique to birds and help them with flight and insulation.','Hard'),
(3,'I am hatched from an egg on land and have scaly skin. I do not have fins. What am I?','Amphibians','Reptiles','Fish','Mammals','Reptiles','Reptiles are land-dwelling animals with dry, scaly skin.','Hard'),
(3,'I am the part of the plant that acts like a factory to make food. What am I?','Roots','Stem','Leaves','Flowers','Leaves','Leaves use sunlight to create food through photosynthesis.','Hard'),
(3,'I am like a highway used by water and nutrients to get to all parts of the plant. What am I?','Roots','Stem','Leaves','Seeds','Stem','The stem transports water from the roots to the leaves and flowers.','Hard'),
(3,'I am found deep under the soil to absorb water and minerals. What am I?','Fruit','Stem','Roots','Leaves','Roots','Roots anchor the plant and drink up water from the ground.','Hard'),
(3,'Just like a pole, I am a steady supporter so the plant will not wither or fall. What am I?','Stem','Roots','Leaves','Petals','Stem','The stem provides the structural support needed for the plant to stand tall.','Hard'),
(3,'I am like an anchor that stays deep in the ground to keep the plant from falling over. What am I?','Leaves','Roots','Stem','Flowers','Roots','Roots anchor the plant firmly in the soil so it doesn''t wash or blow away.','Hard'),
(3,'This type of plant contains parts that are often colorful and sweet-smelling. What is it?','Non-flowering plants','Flowering plants','Grass','Moss','Flowering plants','Flowers use bright colors and scents to attract pollinators like bees.','Hard'),
(3,'These plants, such as ferns or mosses, do not produce seeds or flowers but can still be used in various dishes or decorations. What are they?','Flowering plants','Non-flowering plants','Trees','Fruit plants','Non-flowering plants','Non-flowering plants reproduce via spores instead of seeds and flowers.','Hard'),
(3,'This group of plants, like roses or mango trees, is found in most gardens and villages. What are they?','Unusual plants','Poisonous plants','Common plants','Water plants','Common plants','Common plants are those that are easily found in our everyday environment.','Hard'),
(3,'Children who touch this type of plant often get itchy rashes or skin irritation. What kind of plant is it?','Common plants','Poisonous plants','Water plants','Flowering plants','Poisonous plants','Poisonous plants contain chemicals that can irritate the skin or be harmful if eaten.','Hard'),
(3,'This plant can survive without being watered for a very long time, like a cactus. What is it classified as?','Common plants','Water plants','Unusual plants','Flowering plants','Unusual plants','Unusual plants have special adaptations, like thick stems, to survive in harsh conditions.','Hard'),
(3,'This type of plant can be seen growing underwater when you go snorkeling in the sea. What is it?','Common plants','Water plants','Poisonous plants','Unusual plants','Water plants','Water (aquatic) plants are adapted to live and grow in salt or fresh water.','Hard'),
(3,'Which of these groups do most garden plants belong to because they grow from seeds or buds?','Unusual plants','Common plants','Water plants','Poisonous plants','Common plants','Most common plants we see daily start their life cycle from seeds.','Hard'),
(3,'Inhaling the pollen or accidentally eating parts of this plant can cause nausea and sickness. What is it?','Flowering plant','Poisonous plant','Common plant','Water plant','Poisonous plant','Poisonous plants have toxins that cause negative reactions in humans and animals.','Hard'),
(3,'Which of these does not belong in the group? (Skateboard, Frog, Bag, Clock)','Skateboard','Frog','Bag','Clock','Frog','The frog is a living thing, while the others are non-living objects.','Hard'),
(3,'Which of these does not belong in the group? (Carabao, Tarsier, Bamboo, Doll)','Carabao','Bamboo','Doll','Tarsier','Doll','The doll is a non-living thing, while the others are living organisms.','Hard'),
(3,'Which of these does not belong in the group? (Lizard, Pencil, Book, Phone)','Lizard','Pencil','Book','Phone','Lizard','The lizard is a living thing (animal), while the others are man-made objects.','Hard'),
(3,'Which of these does not belong in the group? (Maya bird, Mouse, Rock, Snake)','Maya bird','Rock','Mouse','Snake','Rock','The rock is non-living matter, whereas the others are all living animals.','Hard'),
(3,'The sirens of the ambulance are getting louder and louder as it approaches. Which sense are you using?','Sense of sight','Sense of smell','Sense of hearing','Sense of taste','Sense of hearing','Your ears detect sound waves and the brain interprets the volume.','Hard'),
(3,'The car is bright yellow. Which sense are you using?','Sense of sight','Sense of touch','Sense of hearing','Sense of smell','Sense of sight','Your eyes detect light and color to identify the appearance of objects.','Hard'),
(3,'The tabletop feels very smooth and cold. Which sense are you using?','Sense of sight','Sense of taste','Sense of touch','Sense of smell','Sense of touch','Nerve endings in your skin detect the texture and temperature of surfaces.','Hard'),
(3,'The ''Sinigang'' soup tastes very sour. Which sense are you using?','Sense of smell','Sense of taste','Sense of hearing','Sense of touch','Sense of taste','Taste buds on your tongue detect chemicals that signal a sour flavor.','Hard'),
